title: Quiz 2 - Ranking & Order
instruction: Directions (21-25): Refer to the data below and answer the questions that follow.   Seven competitive eaters participated in snacks and beverage competition. The persons who participated in both events were I, J, K, L, M, N, and O. The winner was to be selected based upon the time taken to complete the snacks/beverages. Each person completed their snacks/beverages in different time periods, i.e. no two persons completed their snacks/beverages at the same time. Each person obtained a particular position according to his performance. The one who got the top position performed better than others while one who got the lowest position performed worse. I's position in snacks competition was just above N but in beverage competition he was just below K. L's position in beverage competition was just above O but in snacks competition, he was just below M. No persons were assigned positions between I and L in both competitions. At least four persons got positions above I in snacks competition and at least four persons are below him in beverage competition. K did not get the highest or the lowest position in any competition. N's performance was better than O's in both the competitions.
